  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6755 sitting directly on the max negative gamma strike (-8550.2M), dealers are forced to buy this dip aggressively while simultaneously facing massive negative gamma walls below at 6750/6745. The BREAKOUT regime with -8644.6M total GEX means dealers will continue amplifying moves - buying into weakness here but selling any rally back toward the 6800 max positive gamma wall where they'll provide resistance. Watch for continued volatility around these dense negative gamma strikes in the 6745-6765 range, as the recent wall_break and gex_surge events suggest institutional repositioning is driving dealers into reactive hedging mode.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings as dealers amplify both dips toward 6745 and any rallies toward 6800.",
